  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is a two-arm controlled multi-centre trial of two strategies to reduce nosocomial
      MRSA transmission and infection among surgical patients. Enrolment and primary analyses will
      be performed at the hospital level. A total of ten adult surgical departments with at least 3
      surgical subspecialties each will participate in the study. Sites of the study are located in
      9 countries (UK, France, Spain, Germany, Switzerland, Italy, Serbia, Greece and Israel).

      The primary objective is to determine the effect of an early MRSA detection &amp; decolonization
      &amp; isolation strategy compared to an enhanced standard control strategy on
      healthcare-associated MRSA isolation rates among surgical patients at risk of MRSA carriage,
      who are hospitalized for at least 24 hours.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
